Title: Strawberry Shortcake: Bright Lights, Big Dreams

reviewText: I can remember when I was a little girl, I absolutely loved Strawberry Shortcake. I had my room decorated in it, a birthday cake, toys, and yes even undies. When I received the Strawberry Shortcake "Bright Lights Big Dreams" DVD, I was so excited to watch this movie alongside of my little girl. My little girl and I both watched the movie together and really enjoyed it. I loved how, throughout the movie, it gave examples of the difference between right and wrong. I love when my kids watch shows or cartoons that offer some sort of virtue. This movie really helped little girls build their own character, be respectful and make right decisions. This is a great movie for little girls younger then one but can also go up to around eight or nine years old.
Title: Strawberry Shortcake: Bright Lights, Big Dreams

reviewText: I have two daughters (ages 10 and 7) who love the Strawberry Shortcake's Berry Bitty Adventures shows. They've been bummed out because I haven't found the shows on DVD, but since they have been getting released little by little in increments of four as movies, my kids are happy to be able to watch their favorite shows at any time they please. It doesn't matter that it's not new, what matters is that they are seeing something they enjoy, and for kids who want something new, well as of November 1st of this year the American Greetings and Hasbro have made a new season of the series that will air on the Hub channel.

reviewText: For those of you who, like me, are interested in which episodes of "Strawberry Shortcake's Berry Bitty Adventures" are contained on this DVD, here is the list:01. "Strawberry's House Pest" (October 20, 2010) - Strawberry struggles to be the berry best hostess when she has the very worst house guest.02. "Berry Bitty World Record" (October 21, 2010) - Strawberry and friends try to break a Berry Bitty World record to win a vacation for Berrykin Bloom.03. "Different Waltz For Different Faults" (November 3, 2010) - Plum tries to get her friends and the Berrykins to dance like a rival dance team, to win the dance-off trophy.
summary: Contains 3 episodes of "Strawberry Shortcake's Berry Bitty Adventures"
Title: Strawberry Shortcake: Bright Lights, Big Dreams

reviewText: Cute as always but the first episode is really annoying when Jadybug's cousins come to town and are total brats. Between irritating voices and terrible manners I really don't like my daughter watching it. The purpose of the episode it that the girls eventually learn good manners and how to be polite but that only happens in the last 2 minutes. The other two episode on the disc are better though.
